  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a registry study in adult patients with newly diagnosed or refractory/relapsed acute
      myeloid leukemia.

      Investigator's sites: 40 sites in Germany.

      Primary objectives:

        -  Identification of epidemiological data on AML: age, prognostic factors and subgroup
           distributions. Incidence and age distribution are compared with the data of
           population-related tumor registry.

        -  Evaluation of the most important patient-relevant clinical endpoints (outcomes):
           relapse-free survival (RFS) / time to relapse (TTR), calculation of cumulative incidence
           of relapse (CIR) and overall survival (OS)

        -  Documentation of treatment strategy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
